title: BWR - Changelog 02/09/23
content:
Spy
+ Spy sprint with speed boost should match your boosted speed
Fists of Steel
- Fixed reduced overheal building extra ubercharge
~ Fix only works outside of spawn
Dalokohs Bar
+ Reverted recharge time to 10s (was 15s)
- Fixed max overheal increase and uber building bugs
Requisite fixing of bugs, former one to make using spy sprint with the RTR consistent, latter two to avoid unintentionally building uber too fast with a pocketed heavy. Dalokohs recharge was reverted as compensation as it seemed underwhelming without exploits.

Jarate
+ Increased cooldown reduction from extinguishing teameates to -33% (was -20%)
+ Fixed cooldown reduction to be the intended -8s on kill (was -4s)
Mad Milk
+ Increased cooldown reduction from extinguishing teameates to -33% (was -20%)
Gas Passer
+ Increased cooldown reduction from extinguishing teameates to -33% (was -20%)
- Removed cleaning of debuffs in gas cloud
Making the supportive usage of jar weapons more rewarding with the slower recharge. In addition, the gas passer's cloud was not use terribly much for support due to cost of using it and rarity one might need it.

Warrior's Spirit
- Added: No Random Crits
The added damage made the addition of a crit combo somewhat overkill

Backburner
+ Added +33% airblast push force to self
Due to the higher cost of the airblast making its utility more costly, it was felt it should have it's mobility improved to aid in flanking with it without relying on a secondary.

Buffalo Steak Sandvich
- Removed reduction in push force taken from damage
- Removed reduction in airblast vulnerability
Both the speed and knockback made a steak heavy almost unstoppable by normal means, thus reintroducing some counter felt necessary to keep it in check.

Righteous Bison
+ Increased damage bonus to +200%
- Reverted clip size penalty to -33%
Reverting it's clip felt necessary due to its penetration and spammable nature. It's damage was buffed slightly to make up for this, making it more comparable to the shotgun in mid-range.

Conniver's Kunai
+ Increased max health drain restored at 3/s (was 1.5/s)
The regeneration appeared to be far too punishing, requiring over 10 seconds to recover from a single stab. This buff should make it only require at most 20 seconds for your max HP to recover from a chainstab.

Reserve Shooter
+ Removed clip size penalty
- Reduced accuracy bonus to 15% (was 25%)
Panic Attack
- Removed accuracy bonus (was 15% more)
Meant to cut back on excess statistics on items.

Killing Gloves of Boxing
~ Changed On-Kill: gain 100% crits until your next attack or rev up, and 3 second thereafter
+ Crit boost lasts until you start your next rev up or attack
- Crit duration reduced from 5 seconds to 3 seconds (not counting rev time)
With the higher bar to gaining crits, a buff was felt. These changes are meant to make transfering the crits to your next attack more reasonable for the heavy, while keeping the potential duration of crits more limited, particularly with the minigun.

Sharpened Volcano Fragment
- Reduced volcano effect's fire weakness to a +30% vulnerability (was mini-crits)
Given the number of pyro weapons that deal crits/mini-crits on burning enemies, it was felt giving a boost to damage would help prevent overlap and be a better pay-off.

Third Degree
~ Reverted damage link to targets connected by heal beams
+ Linked players includes targets connected through dispeners
+ Removed less healing from healers
Reverted to be more in-line with it's original theme, expanding its use against groups of enemies being healed. Due to the more limited usage, the healing downside was removed.

Quick-Fix
+ Removed ubercharge duration penalty
+ Blast Jump mirroring is toggleable with the RELOAD key
- Blast Jump mirroring makes medic take half the self-damage of their patient
- Reverted ubercharge bonus to +10% (was +33%)
The faster build speed seemed oppressive against other ubers, particularly on limited team sizes. To help with the reverting of its build speed, it's duration was restored, making sharing with teammates even more rewarding. In addition, the blast jumping mirroring was made less free to use but more in the user's control.

title: CF587C AC
CC Wireless Redstone Listener
content:
--Wireless Redstone Control Listener

local output = "back"
local sender_id = 5
local wireless_modem = peripheral.find("modem", function(name, modem)
    return modem.isWireless()
end)
rednet.open(peripheral.getName(wireless_modem))

print("Listening")
while true do
	id, message = rednet.receive()
    if id == sender_id then
        if message == "New" then
			redstone.setAnalogOutput(output, 1)
			os.sleep(1)
			redstone.setAnalogOutput(output, 0)
			print("Received")
		else
			--do nothing
		end
	else
		--do nothing
	end
end

const L = parseInt(readline());
const H = parseInt(readline());
const T = readline();
let output = "";
for (let i = 0; i < H; i++) {
    const ROW = readline();
    // Parcours des caractres du texte  afficher
    for (let j = 0; j < T.length; j++) {
        const letter = T.charAt(j);
        // Dtermination de la plage de caractres correspondant  la lettre
        const alphaBeginning = letter.toUpperCase() === letter ? 'A' : 'a';
        const alphaEnding = letter.toUpperCase() === letter ? 'Z' : 'z';
        let start = 0;
        if (letter < alphaBeginning || letter > alphaEnding) {
            start = ((alphaEnding.charCodeAt(0) - alphaBeginning.charCodeAt(0)) + 1) * L;
        } else {
            start = (letter.charCodeAt(0) - alphaBeginning.charCodeAt(0)) * L;
        }
        output += ROW.substring(start, start + L);
    }
    output += '\n';
}
console.log(output);

 * Vous tes-vous demand comment il serait possible de simuler cet affichage dans un bon vieux terminal ? Nous oui : avec l'art ASCII !
 *
 * Rgles
 * L'art ASCII permet de reprsenter des formes en utilisant des caractres. Dans notre cas, ces formes sont prcisment des mots. Par exemple, le mot "MANHATTAN" pourra tre affich ainsi en art ASCII :
 *

 * Ligne 1 : la largeur L d'une lettre reprsente en art ASCII. Toutes les lettres font la mme largeur.
 *
 * Ligne 2 : la hauteur H d'une lettre reprsente en art ASCII. Toutes les lettres font la mme hauteur.
 *
 * Ligne 3 : La ligne de texte T, compose de N caractres ASCII
 *
 * Lignes suivantes : La chane de caractres ABCDEFGHIJKLMNOPQRSTUVWXYZ? reprsente en art ASCII.

fscanf(STDIN, "%d", $L);
fscanf(STDIN, "%d", $H);

// Lecture de la ligne de texte  afficher en art ASCII (T)
$T = stream_get_line(STDIN, 256 + 1, "\n");

// Conversion du texte en majuscules pour simplifier les correspondances en art ASCII
$T = strtoupper($T);

// Lecture des caractres de l'alphabet en art ASCII
for ($i = 0; $i < $H; $i++)
{
    $ROW = stream_get_line(STDIN, 1024 + 1, "\n");
    $output = '';

    // Parcours des caractres du texte  afficher
    for ($j = 0; $j < strlen($T); $j++) {
        $letter = $T[$j];

        // Dtermination de la plage de caractres correspondant  la lettre
        $alphaBeginning = ctype_upper($letter) ? 'A' : 'a';
        $alphaEnding = ctype_upper($letter) ? 'Z' : 'z';
        $start = 0;

        if (ord($letter) < ord($alphaBeginning) || ord($letter) > ord($alphaEnding)) {
            $start = ((ord($alphaEnding) - ord($alphaBeginning)) + 1) * $L;
        } else {
            $start = (ord($letter) - ord($alphaBeginning)) * $L;
        }

        // Ajout de la partie correspondante de la ligne ROW  la sortie
        $output .= substr($ROW, $start, $L);
    }

    // Affichage de la ligne
    echo($output . "\n");
}

network = peripheral.find("rsBridge")
monitor = peripheral.find("monitor")

function getIngredients(targetItem)
    local cache = {}
    function loadItemData(item, fallback)
        if cache[item] == nil then
            cache[item] = {}

            local storageCount = 0
            local storage = network.getItem({
                name = item
            })
            local recipe = network.getPattern({
                name = item
            })
            cache[item]["recipe"] = recipe
            cache[item]["displayName"] = storage.displayName:match("^%s*%[?(.-)%]?%s*$")
            if cache[item]["displayName"] == "Air" and fallback ~= nil then
                cache[item]["displayName"] = fallback.displayName:match("^%s*%[?(.-)%]?%s*$")
            end

            -- monkey-patching a bug in rsBridge
            if storage ~= nil and storage.amount ~= 0 then
                storageCount = storage.amount
                if storageCount == getCraftingMultiplier(item) and recipe ~= nil then
                    storageCount = 0
                end
            end

            cache[item]["inStorage"] = storageCount
            cache[item]["available"] = storageCount
            cache[item]["needed"] = 0
        end
        return cache[item]
    end

    function getCraftingMultiplier(item)
        local itemData = loadItemData(item)
        if itemData.recipe == nil then
            return 0
        end
        for _, result in pairs(itemData.recipe.outputs) do
            if result.name == item then
                return result.amount
            end
        end
        return 0
    end

    function simplifyRecipeIngredients(recipe)
        local ingredients = {}
        for _, input in pairs(recipe.inputs) do
            input = input[1]
            if input ~= nil and input.amount ~= nil and input.name ~= "minecraft:air" then
                if ingredients[input.name] == nil then
                    ingredients[input.name] = {
                        count = 0,
                        fallback = input
                    }
                end
                ingredients[input.name].count = ingredients[input.name].count + input.amount
            end
        end
        return ingredients
    end

    function mark(item, amount, fallback)
        local itemData = loadItemData(item, fallback)
        itemData.available = itemData.available - amount
        itemData.needed = itemData.needed + amount

        if itemData.available < 0 then
            local multiplier = getCraftingMultiplier(item)
            if multiplier == 0 then
                return
            end

            local craftingCount = math.ceil(-itemData.available / multiplier)

            for input, inputData in pairs(simplifyRecipeIngredients(itemData.recipe)) do
                mark(input, inputData.count * craftingCount, inputData.fallback)
            end
        end
    end

    mark(targetItem, 1)
    local result = {}
    for item, itemData in pairs(cache) do
        if itemData.recipe == nil and itemData.inStorage < itemData.needed then
            result[item] = {
                inStorage = itemData.inStorage,
                needed = itemData.needed,
                displayName = itemData.displayName
            }
        end
    end
    return result
end

function displayIngredients(ingredients)
    monitor.clear()
    monitor.setCursorPos(1, 1)
    for _, itemData in pairs(ingredients) do
        monitor.setTextColor(colors.orange)
        monitor.write(itemData.displayName .. ": ")
        monitor.setTextColor(colors.lightBlue)
        monitor.write(itemData.inStorage .. "")
        monitor.setTextColor(colors.blue)
        monitor.write("/" .. itemData.needed)

        _, cursorPos = monitor.getCursorPos()
        monitor.setCursorPos(1, cursorPos + 1)
    end
end

function startClock()
    while (true) do
        ingredients = getIngredients("allthetweaks:pulsating_black_hole")
        displayIngredients(ingredients)
        sleep(60)
    end
end
startClock()

content:
import numpy as np
from scipy.optimize import newton
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import scienceplots

# Valores de M0 para los que deseas trazar las curvas
M0_values = [
    0.05,
    0.1,
]  # Agrega ms valores segn sea necesario

# Parmetros dados
gamma = 1.4
x_values = np.linspace(1e-1, 1e3, 1000)


# Funcin objetivo que queremos igualar a cero
def equation(ML, M0, x):
    numerator = M0**2 * (1 + (gamma - 1) * ML**2 / 2)
    denominator1 = np.exp(gamma / (gamma + 1) * x)

    # Calculate the logarithm of the problematic term
    exponent = -2 / (gamma + 1) * ((ML**2 - M0**2) / (M0**2 * ML**2))
    log_denominator2 = exponent

    # Calculate the rest of the terms
    denominator3 = 1 + (gamma - 1) * M0**2 / 2

    # Compute the numerator and denominator
    numerator_result = np.log(numerator)
    denominator_result = np.log(denominator1) + log_denominator2 + np.log(denominator3)

    # Calculate the final result by exponentiating the difference of logs
    return np.exp(numerator_result - denominator_result) - ML**2


def solve_p_ratio(ML, Mc):
    epsilon = 1e-6  # Small epsilon to avoid division by zero
    denominator = 1 - (ML / Mc) ** 2
    if np.abs(denominator) < epsilon:
        denominator = np.sign(denominator) * epsilon
    return 1 / np.sqrt(denominator)


# Nmero mximo de iteraciones para la convergencia de Newton-Raphson
max_iterations = 10000

plt.rcParams.update({"text.usetex": True, "font.family": "Helvetica", "font.size": 14})
plt.style.use("science")

fig = plt.subplots(figsize=(12, 8))

# Crear un trazado para cada valor de M0
for M0 in M0_values:
    ML_converged = np.zeros_like(x_values)
    for i, x in enumerate(x_values):
        ML_initial_guess = 1
        ML_converged[i], _ = newton(
            equation,
            ML_initial_guess,
            args=(M0, x),
            maxiter=max_iterations,
            full_output=True,
        )
    p_ratio = solve_p_ratio(M0, ML_converged)
    if np.isclose(p_ratio, 0).any():
        p_ratio[np.isclose(p_ratio, 0)] = np.nan
    plt.plot(x_values, p_ratio, linewidth=2, label=f"$M_0$ = {M0:.2f}")

plt.xlabel("$2*f*L/D_e$")
plt.ylabel("$p0(0)/p(L)$")
plt.xscale("log")
plt.legend()
# plt.ylim(0, 5)
plt.grid(True)
plt.title("Plot of $p0(0)/p(L)$ vs $2*f*L/D_e$ for different $M_0$ values")
plt.show()
